The paper deals with straight line drawings of planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The untangling problem and allocation problem are both graph drawing problems, which are also studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves proving lower bounds and upper bounds for certain graph parameters, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of collinear sets in straight line drawings, which is a topic in computational geometry and information science (cs.SI).
